      "note": "Sustenance may be understood in the sense of all the provision necessary for maintaining physical life as well as mental and spiritual development and wellbeing. Examples of the former are light and rain from heaven and the produce of the earth and facilities of movement on land and sea and in air. Examples of the latter are the moral and spiritual influences that come from our fellow-men, and from the great Teachers and Prophets."
